#. <html><head><title></title><link href="a.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"><meta charset="utf-8"></head><body><hgroup><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.164"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa1"></a><p class="namo">
msgstr "Homage to the Master, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One"

#. </p><h1>
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pi\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </h1><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa2"></a>
msgstr "Venerables, these ninety-two rules entailing confession come up for recitation."

#. </p><hr><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 1: the training rule on lying"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa3"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "Just then Hatthaka the Sakyan had been beaten in debate."

msgstr "While talking with ascetics of other sects, he would assert things after denying them, and he would deny things after asserting them."

msgstr "He evaded the issues, lied, and made sham appointments."

#. <span class="note" hidden>According to <span class="ref">Sp.4.736.6</span> this means: “Before the meal, etc., he would make an appointment, saying, ‘Let there be a debate at such-and-such a time and at such-and-such a place,’ and he would then go there before or after the time of the appointment, saying, ‘Look, sirs, the ascetics of other sects have not come; they are defeated,’ and he would then depart,” <i lang="pi">purebhattādīsu, “asukasmiṃ nāma kāle asukasmiṃ nāma padese vādo hotū”ti saṅketaṃ katvā saṅketato pure vā pacchā vā gantvā, “passatha bho, titthiyā na āgatā parājitā”ti pakkamati</i>.</span>

msgstr "The ascetics of other sects complained and criticized him, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.165\"></a> “When Hatthaka talks with us, how can he assert things after denying them, deny things after asserting them, evade the issues, lie, and make sham appointments?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa4"></a>
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those ascetics of other sects, and they went to Hatthaka and said, “Is it true, Hatthaka, that you are acting in this way?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“These ascetics of other sects should be beaten, whatever it takes."

msgstr "They should not be allowed to win.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "“When Hatthaka talks with ascetics of other sects, how can he assert things after denying them, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.2\"></a> deny things after asserting them, evade the issues, lie, and make sham appointments?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa5"></a>
msgstr "After criticizing Hatthaka in many ways, they informed the Master."

msgstr "The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Hatthaka, “Is it true, Hatthaka, that you are acting in this way?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "“… Foolish man, when you talk with ascetics of other sects, how can you assert things after denying them, deny things after asserting them, evade the issues, lie, and make sham appointments?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.166"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa6"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk lies in full awareness, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa7"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Lies in full awareness</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">the speech of one who is intent on deceiving—"

msgstr "his words, his way of speaking, his breaking into speech, his verbal expression, his eight kinds of ignoble speech:"

msgstr "he says that he has seen what he has not seen;"

msgstr "he says that he has heard what he has not heard;"

msgstr "he says that he has sensed what he has not sensed;"

#. <span class="note" hidden>Although <i lang="pi">muta</i> normally means “thought,” translating as “sensed” is necessary in light of the next paragraph.</span>

msgstr "he says that he has known what he has not known;"

msgstr "he says that he has not seen what he has seen;"

msgstr "he says that he has not heard what he has <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.167\"></a> heard;"

msgstr "he says that he has not sensed what he has sensed;"

msgstr "he says that he has not known what he has known.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa8"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Not seen</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">not seen with the eye.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Not heard</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">not heard with the ear.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Not sensed</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">not smelled with the nose, not tasted with the tongue, not touched with the body.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Not known</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">not known with the mind.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Seen</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">seen with the eye.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Heard</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">heard with the ear.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Sensed</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">smelled with the nose, tasted with the tongue, touched with the body.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Known</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">known with the mind.</span>"

#. </p><h4>
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><h5>
msgstr "Falsely claiming to have experienced what he has not experienced:"

msgstr "a single sense door"

#. </h5><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa9"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa10"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when four conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his view of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa11"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when five conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his view of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his belief of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa12"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when six conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his view of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his belief of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa13"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when seven conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his view of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his belief of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa14"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he says that he has heard what he has not heard …"

msgstr "saying that he has sensed what he has not sensed …"

msgstr "saying that he has known what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.168"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa15"></a>
msgstr "…"

msgstr "when four conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "when five conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "when six conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when seven conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie; while lying, he knows he is lying; after he has lied, he knows he has lied; in misrepresenting his view of what is true; in misrepresenting his belief of what is true; in misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true; in misrepresenting his sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><h5>
msgstr "Falsely claiming to have experienced what he has not experienced:"

msgstr "multiple sense doors"

#. </h5><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa16"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and heard what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and sensed what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and known what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and heard and sensed what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and heard and known what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and heard and sensed and known what he has not seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "<span class=\"note\" hidden>This series seems to be missing one combination: “… saying that he has seen and sensed and known what he has not seen …” Similarly, one combination seems to be missing from <span class="ref">MS. 2.17-2.19</span>.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa17"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and sensed what he has not heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and known what he has not heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and seen what he has not heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and sensed and known what he has not heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and sensed and seen what he has not heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and sensed and known and seen what he has not heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa18"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and known what he has not sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and seen what he has not sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and heard what he has not sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and known and seen what he has not sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and known and heard what he has not sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and known and seen and heard what he has not sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa19"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and heard what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and sensed what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and heard what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and sensed what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and heard and sensed what he has not known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><h5>
msgstr "Falsely claiming not to have experienced what he has experienced"

#. </h5><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa20"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has not seen what he has seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has not heard what he has heard …"

msgstr "saying that he has not sensed what he has sensed …"

msgstr "saying that he has not known what he has known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><h5>
msgstr "Falsely claiming to have experienced with one sense what he has experienced with another"

#. </h5><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa21"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard what he has seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.169\"></a> …"

msgstr "saying that he has sensed what he has seen …"

msgstr "saying that he has known what he has seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has heard and sensed what he has seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has heard and known what he has seen …"

msgstr "saying that he has heard and sensed <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.4\"></a> and known what he seen, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "<span class=\"note\" hidden>This series, too, seems to be missing one combination: “… saying that he has sensed and known what he has seen …” Similarly, one combination seems to be missing from <span class=\"ref\">MS. 2.22-2.24</span>.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa22"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed what he has heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has known what he has heard …"

msgstr "saying that he has seen what he has heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has sensed and known what he has heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has sensed and seen what he has heard …"

msgstr "saying that he has sensed and known and seen what he heard, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa23"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known what he has sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has seen what he has sensed …"

msgstr "saying that he has heard what he has sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen what he has sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has known and heard what he has sensed …"

msgstr "saying that he has known and seen and heard what he sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa24"></a>
msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen what he has known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has heard what he has known …"

msgstr "saying that he has sensed what he has known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "If he lies in full awareness, saying that he has seen and heard what he has known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "saying that he has seen and sensed what he has known …"

msgstr "saying that he has seen and heard and sensed what he known, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

#. </p><h5>
msgstr "Making claims while having doubts"

#. </h5><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa25"></a>
msgstr "If he has doubts about what he has seen, is not sure about what he has seen, does not remember what he has seen, is confused about what he has seen …"

msgstr "If he has doubts about what he has heard, is not sure about what he has heard, does not remember what he has heard, is confused about what he has heard …"

msgstr "If he has doubts about what he has sensed, is not sure about what he has sensed, does not remember what he has sensed, is confused about what he has sensed …"

msgstr "If he has doubts about what he has known, is not sure about what he has known, does not remember what he has known, is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen …"

msgstr "is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and heard …"

msgstr "is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and sensed …"

msgstr "is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and heard …"

msgstr "is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and sensed …"

msgstr "is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and heard and sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when three conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "<span class=\"note\" hidden>This series, too, seems to be missing one combination: “… saying that he has known and heard and sensed what he has seen …”.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa26"></a>
msgstr "…"

msgstr "when four conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "when five conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "when six conditions are fulfilled …"

msgstr "is confused about what he has known, but he lies in full awareness, saying that he has known and seen and heard and sensed, he commits an offense entailing confession when seven conditions are fulfilled:"

msgstr "before he has lied, he knows he is going to lie;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.170"></a>
msgstr "while lying, he knows he is lying;"

msgstr "after he has lied, he knows he has lied;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his view of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his belief of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his acceptance of what is true;"

msgstr "in misrepresenting his sentiment of what is true."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.1.2.7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa27"></a>
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he speaks playfully;"

msgstr "if he is speaks too fast;"

msgstr "(speaks playfully means: speaking quickly; speaks too fast means: thinking to say one thing, he says something else);"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa28"></a>
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on lying, is finished."


#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 2: the training rule on abusive speech"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.2.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.2.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.171"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa29"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were arguing with and abusing good monks."

msgstr "They reviled and insulted them about their caste, name, family, work, craft, illnesses, physical traits, defilements, and offenses, and by calling them names."

msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks from the group of six argue with and abuse good monks?"

msgstr "How can they revile and insult them about these things?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa30"></a>
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they informed the Master. …"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you are acting in this way?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, "

msgstr "“… Foolish men, how can you argue with and abuse good monks?"

msgstr "How can you revile <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.172\"></a> and insult them about their caste, name, family, work, craft, illnesses, physical traits, defilements, and offenses, and by calling them names?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”"

msgstr "… and after rebuking them …"

msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><h5>
msgstr "Jataka"

#. </h5><span class="jataka"><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.2.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa31"></a>
msgstr "“Once upon a time, monks, there was a brahmin in Takkasilā who had an ox called Nandivisāla."

msgstr "On one occasion the ox said to the brahmin, ‘Go, brahmin, and make the following bet worth one thousand coins with a prominent merchant:"

msgstr "“My ox will pull one hundred carts tied together.”’"

msgstr "And that brahmin did just that."

msgstr "Then, after tying one hundred carts together and yoking Nandivisāla to them, he said, ‘Go, you fraud;"

msgstr "pull, you liar.’"

msgstr "But Nandivisāla just stood right there."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Then that brahmin became depressed because he had lost one thousand coins."

msgstr "And Nandivisāla said to him, ‘Why are you depressed?’"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "‘Because I lost one thousand coins because of you.’"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "‘But why did you disgrace me by calling me a fraud when I’m not?"

msgstr "Now go, brahmin, and make the same bet worth two thousand coins with that merchant."

msgstr "But don’t disgrace me by calling me a fraud.’"

msgstr "Once again that brahmin did just that."

msgstr "Then, after <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.173\"></a> tying one hundred carts together and yoking Nandivisāla to them, he said, ‘Go, good ox;"

msgstr "pull, good ox.’"

msgstr "And Nandivisāla pulled those one hundred carts."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa32"></a>
msgstr "One should say what is pleasant,"

#. <br>
msgstr "Never what is unpleasant."

#. <br>
msgstr "For him of pleasant speech,"

#. <br>
msgstr "Heavy loads got carried,"

#. <br>
msgstr "And he obtained wealth;"

#. <br>
msgstr "And he was delighted with that."

#. </p></blockquote></span><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa33"></a>
msgstr "Even at that time, monks, reviling and insulting was unpleasant to me."

msgstr "How then could reviling and insulting be pleasant now?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa34"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk speaks abusively, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.2.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.2.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa35"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Speaks abusively</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">he abuses in ten ways:"

msgstr "about caste, about name, about family, about work, about craft, about illnesses, about physical traits, about defilements, about offenses, and by insulting.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa36"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Caste</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">there are two kinds of castes:"

msgstr "low castes and high castes."

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Low castes</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">outcasts, bamboo workers, hunters, chariot-makers, waste-<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.174\"></a>removers—"

msgstr "these are called “low castes.”</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">High castes</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">aristocrats and brahmins—"

msgstr "these are called “high castes.”</span></span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa37"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Name</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">there are two kinds of names:"

msgstr "low names and high names."

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Low names</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">Avakaṇṇaka, Javakaṇṇaka, Dhaniṭṭhaka, Saviṭṭhaka, Kulavaḍḍhaka, or names, in whatever countries, that are despised, looked down upon, scorned, treated with contempt, disregarded—"

msgstr "these are called “low names.”</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">High names</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">those connected with the Buddha, connected with the Teaching, or connected with the Order, or names, in whatever countries, that are highly regarded, highly thought of, respected, valued, esteemed—"

