msgstr "Indirect abuse"

#. </h5><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa137"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘There are outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers, right here,’ and he’s not speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa138"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘There are aristocrats/brahmins, right here,’ and he’s not speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "…"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa139"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘There are wise ones/competent ones/intelligent ones/learned ones/expounders of the Teaching/those not going to a bad destination/those who can only expect a good destination, right here,’ and he’s not speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa140"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘Perhaps these are outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers,’ and he’s not speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …"

msgstr "<span class=\"note\" hidden>I have added the ellipses points, which are presumably missing in the original due to an editing mistake, cf.<span class=\"ref\">MS.2.138</span> above. The same is true of <span class=\"ref\">MS.2.142</span> below.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa141"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘Perhaps these are wise ones/competent ones/intelligent ones/learned ones/expounders of the Teaching,’ and he’s not speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa142"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘We’re not outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers,’ and he’s not speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "…"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa143"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘We’re not wise ones/we’re not competent ones/we’re not intelligent ones/we’re not learned ones/we’re not expounders of the Teaching/we’re not going to a bad destination/we can only expect a good destination,’<span class=\"note\" hidden>See note in previous rule <span class=\"ref\">MS.2.92</span>.</span> and he’s not <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.14\"></a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.189\"></a> speaking about anyone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Permutations part 2"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.3.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa144"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to yet another who is fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa145"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to one who is not fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa146"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from one who is not fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to another who is fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa147"></a>
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from one who is not fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to another who is not fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.3.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa148"></a>
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he does not want to endear himself;"

msgstr "if he is not aiming at division;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa149"></a>
msgstr "The third rule, the training rule on malicious talebearing, is finished."


#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 4: the training rule on memorizing the Teaching"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.4.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.190"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa150"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were instructing lay followers to memorize the Teaching."

msgstr "Those lay followers became disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards the monks."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa151"></a>
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks from the group of six instruct lay followers to memorize the Teaching, those lay followers becoming disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards the monks?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they informed the Master."

msgstr "…"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you instruct lay followers to memorize the Teaching, those lay followers becoming disrespectful, undeferential, and rude towards the monks?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa152"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk instructs a person who is not fully ordained to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.4.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.4.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa153"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Monk</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">…"

msgstr "The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.191"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa154"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A person who is not fully ordained</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa155"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">To memorize</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">a line, the next line, syllable by syllable, the next phrase."

#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa156"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A line</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">they start together and finish together.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">The next line</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">one of them starts, but they finish together.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Syllable by syllable</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">when ‘<i lang=\"pi\">rūpaṃ aniccaṃ</i>’ is being said, he prompts him, saying, ‘<i lang=\"pi\">rū</i>.’</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">The next phrase</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">when ‘<i lang=\"pi\">rūpaṃ aniccaṃ</i>,’ is being said, the other says, ‘<i lang=\"pi\">vedanā aniccā</i>.’</span>"

msgstr "<a class=\"wt-pa\" id=\"wt-pa157\"></a>And whatever line there is, whatever next line, whatever syllable by syllable, whatever next phrase—"

msgstr "this is all called “to memorize the Teaching.”</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa158"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">The Teaching</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.192\"></a> gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa159"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Instructs</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">if he instructs by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he instructs by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.4.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa160"></a>
msgstr "If it is a person who is not fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as not fully ordained, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a person who is not fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a person who is not fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as fully ordained, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa161"></a>
msgstr "If it is a person who is fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a person who is fully ordained, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is a person who is fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as fully ordained, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.4.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa162"></a>
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he causes a recitation together;"

msgstr "if they practice together;"

msgstr "if he prompts one who is speaking a <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.193\"></a> mostly familiar text;"

msgstr "if he prompts one who is reciting;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><p class="endsutta"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa163"></a>
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on memorizing the Teaching, is finished."


#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 5: the training rule on the same sleeping place"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.5.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.194"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa164"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

msgstr "At that time the lay followers were going to the monastery to listen to the Teaching."

msgstr "When the instruction was over, the senior monks went to their own dwellings, but the newly ordained monks went to sleep right there in the assembly-hall together with the lay people—"

msgstr "mindlessly, thoughtlessly, naked, muttering, and snoring."

msgstr "The lay people complained and criticized them, “How can the Venerables go to sleep mindlessly, thoughtlessly, naked, muttering, and snoring?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa165"></a>
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those lay people, and the monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.16\"></a> and criticized those monks, “How can those monks sleep in the same sleeping place as people who are not fully ordained?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa166"></a>
msgstr "After criticizing those newly ordained monks in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that monks do this?”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.195"></a>
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgstr "How can those foolish men sleep in the same sleeping place as people who are not fully ordained?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa167"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk sleeps in the same sleeping place as a person who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa168"></a>
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.5.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa169"></a>
msgstr "After staying at Āḷavī for as long as he wanted, the Master set out for Kosambī."

msgstr "When he eventually arrived at Kosambī, he stayed at the Badarikā Monastery."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Just then the monks said to Venerable Rāhula, “Rāhula, the Master has laid down a training rule that we cannot sleep in the same sleeping place as a person who’s not fully ordained."

msgstr "Please find another sleeping place.”"

msgstr "Since Rāhula was not able to get a sleeping place, he lay down to sleep in the restroom."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Then, after rising early in the morning, the Master went to the restroom, where he coughed."

msgstr "Rāhula coughed too."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Who’s there?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“It’s me, Master, Rāhula.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Why are you sitting here, Rāhula?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa170"></a>
msgstr "Rāhula informed the <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.196\"></a> Master of what had happened."

msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks, “<strong class=\"rule\">Monks, I allow you to sleep in the same sleeping place as a person who is not fully ordained for two or three nights.</strong>"

msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa171"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk sleeps for more than two or three nights in the same sleeping place as a person who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.5.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.5.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa172"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Monk</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">…"

msgstr "The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa173"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A person who is not fully ordained</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">anyone except a fully ordained monk.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa174"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">For more than two or three nights</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">beyond two or three nights.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa175"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Same</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">together.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa176"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Sleeping place</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">fully roofed, fully walled;"

msgstr "mostly roofed, mostly walled.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa177"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Sleeps […]"

msgstr "in the same sleeping place</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">at dawn on the fourth day:"

msgstr "if he lies down when the person who is not fully ordained is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgstr "if the person who is not fully ordained lies down when he is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgstr "if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgstr "every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.5.3.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.197"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa178"></a>
msgstr "If it is someone who is not fully ordained, and the monk perceives him as not fully ordained, and he sleeps in the same sleeping place as him for more than two or three nights, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is someone who is not fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, and he sleeps in the same sleeping place as him for more than two or three nights, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is someone who is not fully ordained, but the monk perceives him as fully ordained, and he sleeps in the same sleeping place as him for more than two or three nights, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa179"></a>
msgstr "If it is half-roofed and half-walled, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is someone who is fully ordained, but the monk perceives him as not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is someone who is fully ordained, but the monk is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is someone who is fully ordained, and the monk perceives him as fully ordained, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.5.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa180"></a>
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgstr "if he stays together for two or three night;"

msgstr "if he stays together for less than two or three nights;"

msgstr "if, after staying together for two nights, he leaves before dawn on the third night and then stays together again;"

msgstr "if it is fully roofed, but not walled;"

msgstr "if it is fully walled, but not roofed;"

msgstr "if it is mostly not roofed;"

msgstr "if it is mostly not walled;"

msgstr "if the monk sits when the person who is not fully ordained is lying down;"

msgstr "if the person who is not fully ordained sits when the monk is lying down;"

msgstr "if they both sit;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa181"></a>
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on the same sleeping place, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 6: the second training rule on the same sleeping place"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.6.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.198"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa182"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "Just then, while Venerable Anuruddha was walking through the Kosalan country on his way to Sāvatthī, one evening he arrived at a certain village."

msgstr "Just then a woman in that village had prepared her rest house."

msgstr "Anuruddha approached that woman and said, “If it’s not inconvenient for you, I’d like to stay <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.18\"></a> in your rest house for one night.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Please stay, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Other travelers also approached that woman and said, “Madam, if it’s not troublesome for you, we’d like to stay in your rest house for one night.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Sirs, an ascetic is already staying there."

msgstr "If he agrees, you may stay.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Those travelers then approached Anuruddha and said, “Venerable, if it’s not troublesome for you, we’d like to stay one night in the rest house.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Please stay.”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa183"></a>
msgstr "Now as soon as that woman had seen Anuruddha, she had fallen in love with him."

msgstr "She now approached him and said, “Venerable, you won’t be at ease <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.199\"></a> surrounded by these people."

msgstr "It would be good if I prepared a bed for you in the main house.”"

msgstr "Anuruddha consented by remaining silent."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "After preparing a bed in the main house, she put on jewelery and perfume, and she approached Anuruddha and said, “Venerable, you’re good-looking and graceful, and so am I."

msgstr "It would be good, Venerable, if I were to become your wife.”"

msgstr "But Anuruddha remained silent."

msgstr "She said the same thing a second time, but again got no response."

msgstr "And a third time she said, “Venerable, you’re good-looking and graceful, and so am I."

msgstr "It would be good, Venerable, if you took me and all this property.”"

msgstr "But Anuruddha remained silent for a third time."

msgstr "She then threw off her clothes, and she walked up and down, stood, sat down, and lay down in front of him."

msgstr "But Anuruddha controlled his senses and neither looked at nor spoke to her."

msgstr "Then that woman said, “It’s astonishing and amazing."

msgstr "Many people send for me with a hundred or a thousand coins."

msgstr "But this ascetic, even when begged by me, does not want me and all this property.”"

msgstr "After dressing, she fell down <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.200\"></a> with her head at the feet of Anuruddha and said, “Venerable, I’ve committed an offense, in that foolishly, confused, and unskillfully I acted in this way."

msgstr "Venerable, please forgive me for my offense so that I may restrain myself in the future.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Certainly you have committed an offense, in that foolishly, confused, and unskillfully you acted in this way."

msgstr "But since you acknowledge your offense <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.19\"></a> and you make amends for it in accordance with the Teaching, I forgive you."

msgstr "For this is called growth in the training of the noble ones, that is, acknowledging an offense, making amends in accordance with the Teaching, and undertaking restraint for the future.”"



#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa184"></a>
msgstr "The following morning, with her own hands, that woman served and satisfied Anuruddha with various kinds of fine food."

msgstr "When he had finished his meal, she bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgstr "And Anuruddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching."

msgstr "She then said to him, “Wonderful, Venerable, wonderful!"

msgstr "Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what had been hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the darkness so that one with eyes might see what is there—"

msgstr "even so has Anuruddha made the Teaching clear in many ways."

msgstr "Venerable, I go for refuge to the Master and to the Teaching and to the Order of monks."

msgstr "Please <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.201\"></a> accept me as a lay follower who from today has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa185"></a>
msgstr "Soon afterwards, after arriving at Sāvatthī, Anuruddha informed the monks of what had happened."

msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized Anuruddha, “How can Venerable Anuruddha sleep in the same sleeping place as a woman?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa186"></a>
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgstr "“Is it true, Anuruddha, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Anuruddha, how can you sleep in the same sleeping place as a woman?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa187"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk sleeps in the same sleeping place as a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.6.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.6.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa188"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Monk</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">…"

msgstr "The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa189"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A woman</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal;"

msgstr "even a girl born on that very day, all the more an older one.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa190"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Same</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">together.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa191"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Sleeping place</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">fully roofed, fully walled;"

msgstr "mostly roofed, mostly walled.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa192"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Sleeps […] in the same sleeping place</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">when the sun has set:"

msgstr "if the monk lies down when the woman is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgstr "if the woman lies down when <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.202\"></a> the monk is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgstr "if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;"

msgstr "every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.6.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa193"></a>
msgstr "If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he sleeps in the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a woman, but he is unsure if she is, and he sleeps in the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he sleeps in the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa194"></a>
msgstr "If it is half-roofed and half-walled, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If he sleeps in the same sleeping place as a female spirit, a female ghost, a sexual nonconformist, or a female animal, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.6.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa195"></a>
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgstr "if it is fully roofed, but not walled;"

msgstr "if it is fully walled, but not roofed;"

msgstr "if it is mostly not roofed;"

msgstr "if it is mostly not walled;"

msgstr "if the monk sits when the woman is lying down;"

msgstr "if the woman sits when the monk is lying down;"

msgstr "if they both sit down together;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa196"></a>
msgstr "The sixth rule, the second training rule on the same sleeping place, is finished."

#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 7: the training rule on teaching"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.203"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa197"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with and visiting a number of families in Sāvatthī."

msgstr "Then, after dressing one morning, he took his bowl and robe and went to a certain family."

msgstr "Just then the housewife was sitting at the entrance door and the daughter-in-law at the door to one of the rooms."

msgstr "Udāyī went up to the housewife and gave her a teaching, whispering in her ear."

msgstr "And the daughter-in-law thought, “Is this ascetic my mother-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking lewdly?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa198"></a>
msgstr "After teaching the housewife in this way, Udāyī approached the daughter-in-law and gave her a teaching in the same way."

msgstr "Then the housewife thought, “Is this ascetic my daughter-in-law’s lover, or <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.21\"></a> is he speaking lewdly?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "After giving a teaching in this way, Udāyī left."

msgstr "Then the housewife said to her daughter-in-law, “Hey, what did that ascetic say to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“He gave me a teaching, Madam."

msgstr "But what did he say to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“He gave me a teaching, too.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.204"></a>
msgstr "And they complained and criticized him, “How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings by whispering in the ear?"

msgstr "Should not teachings be given audibly and openly?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa199"></a>
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those women, and the monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized Udāyī, “How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings to women?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa200"></a>
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgstr "Foolish man, how can you give teachings to women?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa201"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk gives a teaching to a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa202"></a>
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.205"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa203"></a>
msgstr "Soon afterwards some female lay followers saw some monks and said to them, “Venerables, please give a teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Please just teach five or six sentences."

msgstr "Even with that much it’s possible to understand the Teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”"

msgstr "And being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach them."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Then those female lay followers complained and criticized them, “How can they not teach us when asked?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa204"></a>
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those female lay followers, and they informed the Master."

msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks, “Monks, I allow you to teach five or six sentences to a woman."

msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa205"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa206"></a>
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa207"></a>
msgstr "When the monks from the group of six knew that the Master had made this allowance, they taught women more than five or six sentences in the presence of a man who did not understand."

msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgstr "complained and criticized them, “How can the monks from the group of six teach women more than five or six sentences in the presence of a man who does not understand?”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa208"></a>
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgstr "Foolish men, how can you teach women more than five or six sentences in the presence of a man who doesn’t understand?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.206\"></a> it …"

msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa209"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.4.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa210"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Monk</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">…"

msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa211"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A woman</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal;"

msgstr "one who understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is lewd and what is not lewd.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa212"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">More than five or six sentences</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">in excess of five or six sentences.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa213"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A teaching</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa214"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Gives</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">if he teaches by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If he teaches by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa215"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Except in the presence of a man who understands</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">unless a man who understands is present."

msgstr "<span class=\"note\" hidden>“Is present” is not actually found in the Pali, but it is implied.</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A man who understands</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">one who is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is lewd and what is not lewd.</span></span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.4.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa216"></a>
msgstr "If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgstr "If it is a woman, but he is unsure if it is, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.207"></a>
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa217"></a>
msgstr "If he teaches more than five or six sentences to a female spirit, a female ghost, a sexual nonconformist, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.23\"></a> or a female animal in the form of a woman, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgstr "If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.7.4.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa218"></a>
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgstr "if a man who understands is present;"

msgstr "if he teaches five or six sentences;"

msgstr "if he teaches less than five or six sentences;"

msgstr "if he gets up and then sits down again and teaches;"

msgstr "if the woman gets up and then sits down again, and he then teaches her;<span class=\"note\" hidden><i lang=\"pi\">Tasmiṃ deseti</i>. According to <span class=\"ref\">Sp.4.751.8</span> this locative should be read as a dative.</span>"

msgstr "if he teaches another woman;"

msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgstr "if he is asked a question and then speaks;"

msgstr "if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and a woman listens in;"

msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa219"></a>
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on teaching, is finished."


#. </p><hgroup><h1>
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 8: the training rule on informing truthfully"

#. </h1></hgroup><h2>
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.8.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.8.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.208"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa220"></a>
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgstr "Just then a number of monks who were friends had entered the rains on the banks of the river Vaggumudā."

msgstr "Just then Vajjī was short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops blighted and turned to straw, and it was not easy to get by on almsfood."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The monks considered the difficult circumstances, and they thought, “How can we remain united and in harmony, have a comfortable rains, and get almsfood without problems?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Some said, “We could do work for the householders, and they’ll give something in return."

msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Some said, “There’s no need to do work for the householders."

msgstr "Let’s instead take messages for them, and they’ll give something in return."

msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Some said, “There’s no need to do work for the householders, nor to take messages for them."

msgstr "Let’s instead praise one another’s <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.209\"></a> superhuman qualities to the householders, ‘Such a monk has the first <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.24\"></a> absorption, such a monk the second absorption, such a monk the third, such a monk the fourth;"

msgstr "such a monk is a stream-enterer, such a monk a once-returner, such a non-returner, such a perfected one;"

msgstr "such a monk has the three true insights, and such the six direct knowledges.’"

msgstr "Then they’ll give to us."

msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort and have no problems getting almsfood."

msgstr "Indeed, this is the better way, that we praise one another’s superhuman qualities to the householders.”"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa221"></a>
msgstr "Then they praised each other’s superhuman qualities to the householders, “Such a monk has the first absorption …"

msgstr "such a monk has the six direct knowledges.”"

msgstr "And those people thought, “We’re fortunate that such monks have come to us for the rains."

msgstr "Such monks as these, who are virtuous and of good character, have never before entered the rains with us.”"

msgstr "And they gave such food and drink to those monks that they did not even eat and drink themselves, or give to their parents, to their wives and children, to their slaves, servants, and workers, to their friends and companions, or to their relatives."

msgstr "In this way those monks became handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, and clear skin."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.8.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa222"></a>
msgstr "Now it was the custom for monks who had finished keeping the rains to go and see the Master."

msgstr "So when the rainy-season residence was completed and the three months had elapsed, those monks put their dwellings in order, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.210\"></a> took their bowls and robes, and departed for Vesālī."

msgstr "When they eventually arrived at Vesālī, they went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgstr "There they approached the Master, bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "At that time the monks who had completed the rainy-season residence in that region were thin, haggard and pale, their veins protruding all over their limbs."

msgstr "But the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā were handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, and clear skin."

#. </p><p>
msgstr "It is the custom for Buddhas to greet visiting monks, and so the Master <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.25\"></a> said to them, “I hope you’re keeping well, monks, I hope you’re comfortable;"

msgstr "I hope you spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute, and that you had no trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“We’re keeping well, Master, we’re comfortable;"

msgstr "we spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute, and we had no trouble getting almsfood.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "Buddhas sometimes ask knowing, and knowing sometimes do not ask;"

msgstr "they ask knowing the right time to ask, and they ask knowing the right time not to ask."

msgstr "Buddhas ask when it is beneficial, not when it is unbeneficial;"

msgstr "in regard to what is unbeneficial, the Buddhas have destroyed the bridge."

msgstr "Buddhas question the monks for two reasons:"

msgstr "to give a teaching or to lay down a training rule."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa223"></a>
msgstr "And the Master said to those monks, “In what way, monks, did you spend the rains at ease, without having any trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "And they informed the Master of what had happened."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.211"></a>
msgstr "“But had you really achieved those superhuman qualities?”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "“Yes, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “Monks, how can you for the sake of your stomachs praise one another’s superhuman qualities to householders?"

msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa224"></a>
msgstr "‘If a monk truthfully informs a person who is not fully ordained of a superhuman quality, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.8.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.8.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa225"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">whoever …</span>"

msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Monk</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">…"

msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa226"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A person who is not fully ordained</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa227"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A superhuman quality</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in solitude.</span>"

#. </p><h2>
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa228"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Absorption</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">the first absorption, the second absorption, the third absorption, the fourth absorption.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa229"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Release</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">emptiness release, signless release, desireless release.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa230"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Stillness</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">emptiness stillness, signless stillness, desireless stillness.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa231"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Attainment</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">emptiness attainment, signless attainment, desireless attainment.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa232"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Knowledge and vision</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">the three true insights.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa233"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Development of the path</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">the four applications of mindfulness, the four right efforts, the four bases of supernormal power, the five spiritual faculties, the five spiritual powers, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.212\"></a> the seven factors of awakening, the noble eightfold path.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa234"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Realization of the fruits</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">realization of the fruit of stream-entry, realization of the fruit of once-returning, realization of the fruit of non-returning, realization of perfection.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa235"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Abandoning the defilements</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">the abandoning of sensual desire, the abandoning of ill-will, the abandoning of confusion.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa236"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">A mind without hindrances</strong>:"

msgstr ""
"<span class=\"gloss\">a mind without sensual desire, a mind without ill-will, a mind without confusion.</span>"

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa237"></a>
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Delighting in solitude</strong>:"

msgstr "<span class=\"gloss\">because of the first absorption there is delight in solitude, because of the second absorption there is delight in solitude, because of the third absorption there is delight in solitude, because of the fourth absorption there is delight in solitude.</span>"

#. </p><h4>
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><h5>
msgstr "First absorption"


#. </h5><p><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pc.8.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa238"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa239"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I’m attaining the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa240"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I’ve attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa241"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I obtain the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa242"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I master the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa243"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I’ve realized the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h5>
msgstr "Other individual attainments"

#. </h5><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa244"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I attained the second absorption …"

msgstr "the third absorption …"

msgstr "the fourth absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained …"

msgstr " I obtain … I master …"

msgstr "I’ve realized the fourth absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa245"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I attained the emptiness release …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.213"></a>
msgstr "the signless release …"

msgstr "the desireless release …"

msgstr "the emptiness stillness …"

msgstr "the signless stillness …"

msgstr "the desireless stillness … I’m attaining … I’ve attained …"

msgstr " I obtain … I master …"

msgstr "I’ve realized the desireless stillness,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa246"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I attained the emptiness attainment …"

msgstr "the signless attainment …"

msgstr "the desireless attainment … I’m attaining … I’ve attained …"

msgstr " I obtain … I master …"

msgstr "I’ve realized the desireless attainment,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa247"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I attained the three true insights … I’m attaining … I’ve attained …"

msgstr " I obtain … I master …"

msgstr "I’ve realized the three true insights,” he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa248"></a>
msgstr "Informs:"

msgstr "if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained,"

msgstr "“I attained the four <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.27\"></a> applications of mindfulness …"

msgstr "the four right efforts …"

msgstr "the four bases for supernormal power … I’m attaining … I’ve attained …"

